12 "§ 126A-76. Flexible compensation plan.
13 (a) The Director of OSHR may provide eligible officers and employees of State agencies
14 not covered by the provisions of G.S. 116-17.2 a program of dependent care assistance as
15 available under section 129 and related sections of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as
16 amended. The Director of OSHR may authorize State agencies to enter into annual agreements
17 with employees who elect to participate in the program to provide for a reduction in salary. With
18 the approval of the Director of OSHR, savings in the employer's share of contributions under the
19 Federal Insurance Contributions Act on account of the reduction in salary may be used to pay
20 some or all of the administrative expenses of the program. Should the Director of OSHR decide
21 to contract with a third party to administer the terms and conditions of a program of dependent
22 care assistance, the Director of OSHR may select a contractor only upon a thorough and
23 completely competitive procurement process.
24 (b) Notwithstanding any other provisions of law relating to the salaries of officers and
25 employees of State agencies, the Director of OSHR may provide a plan of flexible compensation
26 to eligible officers and employees of State agencies, not covered by the provisions of
27 G.S. 116-17.2 for benefits available under section 125 and related sections of the Internal
28 Revenue Code of 1986, as amended. This plan shall not replace, substitute for, or duplicate any
29 benefits provided to employees and officers under Article 1A of Chapter 120 of the General
30 Statutes, Articles 1, 3B, 4, and 6 of Chapter 135 of the General Statutes. The plan may, however,
31 include offerings for products and benefits that are supplemental or additional to these statutory
32 benefits. If a plan of flexible compensation is offered, then a TRICARE supplement shall be
33 offered.
