50 "Article 10.
51 "Inappropriate Political Activity.
Page 26 Senate Bill 1041-First Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 "§ 126A-100. Appropriate political activity of State employees defined.
2 (a) Each State employee retains all the rights and obligations of citizenship provided in
3 the Constitution and laws of the State of North Carolina and the Constitution and laws of the
4 United States of America; however, no State employee subject to this Chapter or temporary State
5 employee shall:
6 (1) Take any active part in managing a campaign, or campaign for political office
7 or otherwise engage in political activity while on duty or within any period of
8 time during which he is expected to perform services for which he receives
9 compensation from the State;
10 (2) Otherwise use the authority of their State position, or utilize State funds,
11 supplies or vehicles to secure support for or oppose any candidate, party, or
12 issue in an election involving candidates for office or party nominations, or
13 affect the results thereof.
14 (b) No head of any agency or other State employee exercising supervisory authority shall
15 make, issue, or enforce any rule or policy the effect of which is to interfere with the right of any
16 State employee as an individual to engage in political activity while not on duty or at times during
17 which he is not performing services for which he receives compensation from the State. A State
18 employee who is or may be expected to perform his duties on a twenty-four hour per day basis
19 shall not be prevented from engaging in political activity except during regularly scheduled
20 working hours or at other times when actually performing the duties of office. The willful
21 violation of this subdivision shall be a Class 1 misdemeanor.
22 "§ 126A-101. Promise or threat to obtain political contribution or support.
23 (a) It is unlawful for a State employee or a person appointed to State office, other than
24 elective office or office on a board, commission, committee, or council whose function is
25 advisory only, whether or not subject to this Article, to coerce:
26 (1) a State employee subject to this Article,
27 (2) an applicant for a position subject to this Article
28 to support or contribute to a political candidate, political committee as defined in G.S. 163-278.6,
29 or political party or to change the party designation of the individual's voter registration by
30 threatening that change in employment status or discipline or preferential personnel treatment
31 will occur with regard to an individual listed in subdivisions (1)and (2) of this subsection.
32 (a1) It is unlawful for a public servant as defined in G.S. 138A-3(70)a. to coerce a person
33 as described in G.S. 138A-32(d)(1), (2), or (3) to support or contribute to a political candidate, a
34 political committee as defined in G.S. 163-278.6, or a political party by threatening discipline or
35 promising preferential treatment with regard to that person's business with the individual's State
36 office or that person's activities regulated by the individual's State office.
37 (b) Any person violating this section shall be guilty of a Class 2 misdemeanor.
38 (c) A State employee subject to this Article who without probable cause falsely accuses
39 a State employee or a person appointed to State office of violating this section shall be subject to
40 discipline or change in employment status in accordance with the provisions of G.S. 126A-81
41 and may, as otherwise provided by law, be subject to criminal penalties for perjury or civil
42 liability for libel, slander, or malicious prosecution.
43 "§ 126A-102. Threat to obtain political contribution or support.
44 (a) It is unlawful for any person to coerce:
45 (1) a State employee subject to this Article,
46 (2) an applicant for a position subject to this Article
47 to support or contribute to a political candidate, political committee as defined in G.S. 163-278.6,
48 or political party or to change the party designation of his or her voter registration by explicitly
49 threatening that change in employment status or discipline or preferential personnel treatment
50 will occur with regard to any person listed in subdivisions (1) and (2) of this subsection.
51 (b) Any person violating this section shall be guilty of a Class 2 misdemeanor.
