16 "Article 16.
17 "The Privacy of State Employee Personnel Records.
18 "§ 126A-160. Rules and regulations.
19 The Commission shall prescribe such rules or policies as it deems necessary to implement
20 the provisions of this Article.
21 "§ 126A-161. Personnel files not subject to inspection under G.S. 132-6.
22 (a) Except as provided in G.S. 126A-162 and G.S. 126A-163, personnel files of State
23 employees shall not be subject to inspection and examination as authorized by G.S. 132-6.
24 (b) The following definitions apply in this Article:
25 (1) Employee. – A current State employee, former State employee, or applicant
26 for State employment.
27 (2) Employer. – Any State department, university, division, bureau, commission,
28 council, or other agency subject to Article 16 of this Chapter.
29 (3) Personnel file. – Any employment-related or personal information gathered
30 by an employer or by OSHR. Employment-related information contained in a
31 personnel file includes information related to an individual's application,
32 selection, promotion, demotion, transfer, leave, salary, contract for
33 employment, benefits, suspension, performance evaluation, disciplinary
34 actions, and termination. Personal information contained in a personnel file
35 includes an individual's home address, social security number, medical
36 history, personal financial data, marital status, dependents, and beneficiaries.
37 (4) Record. – The personnel information that each employer is required to
38 maintain in accordance with G.S. 126A-162.
39 (c) Personnel files of former State employees who have been separated from State
40 employment for 10 or more years may be open to inspection and examination except for papers
41 and documents relating to demotions and to disciplinary actions resulting in the dismissal of the
42 employee. Retirement files maintained by the Retirement Systems Division of the Department
43 of State Treasurer shall be made public pursuant to G.S. 128-33.1 and G.S. 135-6.1.
44 "§ 126A-162. Certain records to be kept by State agencies open to inspection.
45 (a) Each agency shall maintain a record of each of its employees, showing the following
46 information with respect to each such employee:
47 (1) Name.
48 (2) Date of original employment or appointment to State service.
49 (3) The terms of any contract by which the employee is employed whether written
50 or oral, past and current, to the extent that the agency has such record in its
51 possession.
