6 "§ 126A-186. Statutes that imply exemptions from this Chapter.
7 Where a State law specifies a process for a position that is inconsistent with the process
8 established in this Chapter, the position is exempt from this Chapter to that extent. For example,
9 and not by way of limitation:
10 (1) A statute that identifies someone as being "appointed by" an agency head
11 makes that position exempt from Article 5 of this Chapter.
12 (2) A statute that identifies someone as serving "at the pleasure of" an agency
13 head makes that position exempt from Article 8 of this Chapter.
14 "§ 126A-187. Agency discretion to adopt policies for exempt employees.
15 When a statute makes a position exempt from this Chapter regarding any subject, an agency
16 has discretion to address that subject by adopting either its own policy or the Commission policy.
